## Notes for advocates

The strongest pro-demonstrated path is that multiple credible outlets reported public release before May 8, described the document as a purported/alleged suicide note, quoted language about choosing one's time to say goodbye, and identified a federal judge/court-file release.

The strongest not-demonstrated path is that those same outlets used hedging language, reported lack of independent verification or official authentication, and left uncertainty about whether the note was intended as a suicide note rather than another communication later characterized as one.
